# Session Authentication
"""
User gives uname, psswd -> session_id
session_id -> gets stored in browser
user's each request has session_id
backend checks for session_id and validates user
"""
# JWT Authentication
"""
User gives uname, psswd -> JWT token(access token(short lived) + refresh token(long lived)) 
with user's each request access_token is sent
in backend verifies the access_token, if valid it gives access to the API/request
if invalid -> uses refresh token to generate a new access token
if refresh_token is invalid -> then user gives uname psswd again to gain new access and refresh token
"""

# endpoint/api/view - login